<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272880>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 90–97. Arganthomyza vittipennis (Walker, 1857), male (Canada: Ontario). 90 – external genitalia, caudally; 91 – the same, laterally; 92 – hypandrial complex, laterally; 93 – base of phallapodeme, dorsally; 94 – transandrium, caudally; 95 – apex of nlum, anteroventrally (widest extension); 96 – aedeagal complex, laterally; 97 – gonostylus, lateroventrally (widest extension). Scales = 0.05 mm (Figs 95, 97) and 0.1 mm (others)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4272880/files/figure.png" .

